Note:
Runa Standard Library: UDP Protocol Implementation

Production-grade UDP (User Datagram Protocol) implementation providing
connectionless, lightweight, message-oriented network communication
with advanced features for high-performance applications.

Features:
- Full UDP/IP stack implementation with RFC compliance
- Connectionless datagram transmission with minimal overhead
- Multicast and broadcast messaging support
- UDP socket options and configuration management
- Message queuing and buffering with size limits
- Network address resolution and port management
- UDP hole punching for NAT traversal
- Packet fragmentation and reassembly handling
- Quality of Service (QoS) and traffic shaping
- Real-time communication optimizations
- UDP-based protocol implementations (DNS, DHCP, SNMP)
- Performance monitoring and statistics collection
- Error detection and handling mechanisms
- IPv4 and IPv6 dual-stack support
- Security features and access control
:End Note

Import "../../collections" as Collections
Import "../../string" as String
Import "../../datetime" as DateTime
Import "net/socket" as Socket
Import "net/net" as Net

Note: UDP socket and endpoint types
Type called "UDPSocket":
    socket_id as String
    base_socket as Socket.Socket
    local_endpoint as UDPEndpoint
    remote_endpoint as UDPEndpoint
    state as UDPSocketState
    options as UDPOptions
    message_queue as UDPMessageQueue
    statistics as UDPStatistics
    multicast_groups as List[String]
    broadcast_enabled as Boolean

Type UDPSocketState is:
    | Created
    | Bound
    | Connected
    | Listening
    | Closed

Type called "UDPEndpoint":
    ip_address as String
    port as Integer
    address_family as String
    interface_name as String

Type called "UDPOptions":
    receive_buffer_size as Integer
    send_buffer_size as Integer
    receive_timeout as Float
    send_timeout as Float
    reuse_address as Boolean
    reuse_port as Boolean
    broadcast as Boolean
    multicast_ttl as Integer
    multicast_loop as Boolean
    dont_fragment as Boolean
    type_of_service as Integer

Note: UDP message types
Type called "UDPMessage":
    message_id as String
    source_endpoint as UDPEndpoint
    destination_endpoint as UDPEndpoint
    data as String
    length as Integer
    timestamp as DateTime.DateTime
    ttl as Integer
    priority as Integer
    checksum as Integer

Type called "UDPMessageQueue":
    queue_id as String
    messages as List[UDPMessage]
    max_size as Integer
    current_size as Integer
    total_received as Integer
    total_sent as Integer
    dropped_messages as Integer
    queue_full_count as Integer

Type called "UDPDatagram":
    source_port as Integer
    destination_port as Integer
    length as Integer
    checksum as Integer
    data as String
    timestamp as DateTime.DateTime

Note: UDP server and client types
Type called "UDPServer":
    server_id as String
    bind_endpoint as UDPEndpoint
    socket as UDPSocket
    message_handlers as Dictionary[String, String]
    client_registry as UDPClientRegistry
    access_control as UDPAccessControl
    is_running as Boolean
    server_options as UDPServerOptions
    statistics as UDPServerStatistics

Type called "UDPClient":
    client_id as String
    socket as UDPSocket
    server_endpoint as UDPEndpoint
    client_options as UDPClientOptions
    connection_state as String
    retry_policy as UDPRetryPolicy
    statistics as UDPClientStatistics

Type called "UDPServerOptions":
    max_message_size as Integer
    message_timeout as Float
    enable_broadcast as Boolean
    enable_multicast as Boolean
    thread_pool_size as Integer
    rate_limiting as Boolean
    max_clients as Integer

Type called "UDPClientOptions":
    connect_timeout as Float
    retry_count as Integer
    retry_delay as Float
    keep_alive_interval as Float
    automatic_reconnect as Boolean

Note: Multicast and broadcast support
Type called "UDPMulticastGroup":
    group_address as String
    group_port as Integer
    interface_address as String
    members as List[UDPEndpoint]
    ttl as Integer
    is_active as Boolean
    creation_time as DateTime.DateTime

Type called "UDPBroadcastDomain":
    network_address as String
    subnet_mask as String
    broadcast_address as String
    enabled_interfaces as List[String]
    broadcast_rate_limit as Integer

Note: Security and access control
Type called "UDPAccessControl":
    enabled as Boolean
    allowed_sources as List[String]
    blocked_sources as List[String]
    allowed_ports as List[Integer]
    blocked_ports as List[Integer]
    rate_limits as Dictionary[String, UDPRateLimit]
    message_size_limit as Integer
    connection_limits as Dictionary[String, Integer]

Type called "UDPRateLimit":
    messages_per_second as Integer
    bytes_per_second as Integer
    current_message_count as Integer
    current_byte_count as Integer
    window_start as DateTime.DateTime
    window_duration as Float
    exceeded as Boolean

Type called "UDPClientRegistry":
    registry_id as String
    clients as Dictionary[String, UDPClientInfo]
    max_clients as Integer
    cleanup_interval as Integer
    last_cleanup as DateTime.DateTime

Type called "UDPClientInfo":
    client_endpoint as UDPEndpoint
    first_seen as DateTime.DateTime
    last_seen as DateTime.DateTime
    message_count as Integer
    bytes_transferred as Integer
    is_active as Boolean

Note: Performance and statistics
Type called "UDPStatistics":
    messages_sent as Integer
    messages_received as Integer
    bytes_sent as Integer
    bytes_received as Integer
    send_errors as Integer
    receive_errors as Integer
    dropped_messages as Integer
    duplicate_messages as Integer
    out_of_order_messages as Integer
    checksum_errors as Integer
    fragmentation_events as Integer
    reassembly_failures as Integer

Type called "UDPServerStatistics":
    total_clients as Integer
    active_clients as Integer
    messages_processed as Integer
    bytes_processed as Integer
    processing_errors as Integer
    uptime as Integer
    peak_clients as Integer
    average_message_size as Float
    peak_message_rate as Integer

Type called "UDPClientStatistics":
    connection_attempts as Integer
    successful_connections as Integer
    failed_connections as Integer
    messages_sent as Integer
    messages_received as Integer
    timeouts as Integer
    retries as Integer

Type called "UDPRetryPolicy":
    max_retries as Integer
    initial_delay as Float
    max_delay as Float
    backoff_multiplier as Float
    jitter as Boolean

Note: UDP socket operations
Process called "create_udp_socket" returns UDPSocket:
    Return UDPSocket with:
    socket_id as generate_udp_socket_id()
    base_socket as Socket.create_udp_socket()
    local_endpoint as UDPEndpoint with ip_address as "0.0.0.0" and port as 0 and address_family as "IPv4" and interface_name as ""
    remote_endpoint as UDPEndpoint with ip_address as "" and port as 0 and address_family as "IPv4" and interface_name as ""
    state as Created
    options as create_default_udp_options()
    message_queue as create_udp_message_queue()
    statistics as create_udp_statistics()
    multicast_groups as list
    broadcast_enabled as false

Process called "bind_udp_socket" that takes socket as UDPSocket and ip_address as String and port as Integer returns Boolean:
    If socket.state is not Created:
    Return false Let socket_address be Socket.SocketAddress with:
    family as Socket.IPv4
    ip_address as ip_address
    port as port
    unix_path as ""
    scope_id as 0 Let bind_success be Socket.bind_socket with socket as socket.base_socket and address as socket_address
    If not bind_success:
    Return false Set socket.local_endpoint.ip_address to ip_address
    Set socket.local_endpoint.port to port
    Set socket.state to Bound Return true

Process called "connect_udp_socket" that takes socket as UDPSocket and remote_ip as String and remote_port as Integer returns Boolean:
    If socket.state is not Bound and socket.state is not Created:
    Return false Let connect_success be Socket.connect_socket_to_address with socket as socket.base_socket and ip_address as remote_ip and port as remote_port
    If not connect_success:
    Return false Set socket.remote_endpoint.ip_address to remote_ip
    Set socket.remote_endpoint.port to remote_port
    Set socket.state to Connected Return true

Process called "send_udp_message" that takes socket as UDPSocket and data as String returns Integer:
    If socket.state is not Connected and socket.state is not Bound:
    Return 0 If String.length with str as data is greater than socket.options.send_buffer_size:
    Set socket.statistics.send_errors to socket.statistics.send_errors 1
    Return 0 Let bytes_sent be Socket.send_data with socket as socket.base_socket and data as data
    If bytes_sent is greater than 0:
    Set socket.statistics.messages_sent to socket.statistics.messages_sent 1
    Set socket.statistics.bytes_sent to socket.statistics.bytes_sent bytes_sent Let message be create_udp_message with source as socket.local_endpoint and destination as socket.remote_endpoint and data as data
    add_message_to_queue with queue as socket.message_queue and message as message and is_outgoing as true Return bytes_sent

Process called "send_udp_message_to" that takes socket as UDPSocket and data as String and destination as UDPEndpoint returns Integer:
    If socket.state is not Bound:
    Return 0 If String.length with str as data is greater than socket.options.send_buffer_size:
    Set socket.statistics.send_errors to socket.statistics.send_errors 1
    Return 0 Note: Use sendto for unconnected UDP sockets
    Let bytes_sent be Socket.sendto_data with socket as socket.base_socket and data as data and address as create_socket_address_from_udp_endpoint with endpoint as destination If bytes_sent is greater than 0:
    Set socket.statistics.messages_sent to socket.statistics.messages_sent 1
    Set socket.statistics.bytes_sent to socket.statistics.bytes_sent bytes_sent Let message be create_udp_message with source as socket.local_endpoint and destination as destination and data as data
    add_message_to_queue with queue as socket.message_queue and message as message and is_outgoing as true Return bytes_sent

Process called "receive_udp_message" that takes socket as UDPSocket returns UDPMessage:
    If socket.state is not Connected and socket.state is not Bound:
    Return None If socket.state is Connected:
    Let data be Socket.receive_data with socket as socket.base_socket and buffer_size as socket.options.receive_buffer_size
    If data is not equal to "":
    Set socket.statistics.messages_received to socket.statistics.messages_received 1
    Set socket.statistics.bytes_received to socket.statistics.bytes_received String.length with str as data Return create_udp_message with source as socket.remote_endpoint and destination as socket.local_endpoint and data as data Otherwise:
    Let receive_result be Socket.recvfrom_data with socket as socket.base_socket and buffer_size as socket.options.receive_buffer_size
    If receive_result is not None and "data" in receive_result and "address" in receive_result:
    Let data be receive_result["data"] as String
    Let sender_address be receive_result["address"] as Socket.SocketAddress Set socket.statistics.messages_received to socket.statistics.messages_received 1
    Set socket.statistics.bytes_received to socket.statistics.bytes_received String.length with str as data Let source_endpoint be create_udp_endpoint_from_socket_address with address as sender_address
    Return create_udp_message with source as source_endpoint and destination as socket.local_endpoint and data as data Return None

Process called "close_udp_socket" that takes socket as UDPSocket:
    Socket.close_socket with socket as socket.base_socket
    Set socket.state to Closed

Note: UDP server implementation
Process called "create_udp_server" that takes bind_ip as String and port as Integer returns UDPServer:
    Return UDPServer with:
    server_id as generate_udp_server_id()
    bind_endpoint as UDPEndpoint with ip_address as bind_ip and port as port and address_family as "IPv4" and interface_name as ""
    socket as create_udp_socket()
    message_handlers as dictionary
    client_registry as create_udp_client_registry()
    access_control as create_default_udp_access_control()
    is_running as false
    server_options as create_default_udp_server_options()
    statistics as create_udp_server_statistics()

Process called "start_udp_server" that takes server as UDPServer returns Boolean:
    If server.is_running:
    Return false Let bind_success be bind_udp_socket with socket as server.socket and ip_address as server.bind_endpoint.ip_address and port as server.bind_endpoint.port
    If not bind_success:
    Return false Set server.is_running to true Note: Configure socket options
    configure_udp_server_socket with server as server Return true

Process called "stop_udp_server" that takes server as UDPServer:
    Set server.is_running to false
    close_udp_socket with socket as server.socket

Process called "handle_udp_server_message" that takes server as UDPServer returns Boolean:
    If not server.is_running:
    Return false Let message be receive_udp_message with socket as server.socket
    If message is None:
    Return false Note: Check access control
    If not check_udp_access with access_control as server.access_control and source as message.source_endpoint:
    Return false Note: Update client registry
    update_client_registry with registry as server.client_registry and endpoint as message.source_endpoint Note: Process message based on handlers
    let message_type be determine_message_type with data as message.data
    If message_type in server.message_handlers:
    let handler as server.message_handlers[message_type]
    process_udp_message_with_handler with server as server and message as message and handler as handler Set server.statistics.messages_processed to server.statistics.messages_processed 1
    Set server.statistics.bytes_processed to server.statistics.bytes_processed message.length Return true

Process called "send_udp_server_response" that takes server as UDPServer and response_data as String and client_endpoint as UDPEndpoint returns Boolean:
    If not server.is_running:
    Return false Let bytes_sent be send_udp_message_to with socket as server.socket and data as response_data and destination as client_endpoint
    Return bytes_sent is greater than 0

Note: UDP client implementation
Process called "create_udp_client" returns UDPClient:
    Return UDPClient with:
    client_id as generate_udp_client_id()
    socket as create_udp_socket()
    server_endpoint as UDPEndpoint with ip_address as "" and port as 0 and address_family as "IPv4" and interface_name as ""
    client_options as create_default_udp_client_options()
    connection_state as "disconnected"
    retry_policy as create_default_udp_retry_policy()
    statistics as create_udp_client_statistics()

Process called "connect_udp_client" that takes client as UDPClient and server_ip as String and server_port as Integer returns Boolean:
    Set client.server_endpoint.ip_address to server_ip
    Set client.server_endpoint.port to server_port Let connect_success be connect_udp_socket with socket as client.socket and remote_ip as server_ip and remote_port as server_port
    If connect_success:
    Set client.connection_state to "connected"
    Set client.statistics.connection_attempts to client.statistics.connection_attempts 1
    Set client.statistics.successful_connections to client.statistics.successful_connections 1
    Return true Set client.statistics.connection_attempts to client.statistics.connection_attempts 1
    Set client.statistics.failed_connections to client.statistics.failed_connections 1
    Return false

Process called "send_udp_client_message" that takes client as UDPClient and data as String returns Boolean:
    If client.connection_state is not equal to "connected":
    Return false Let bytes_sent be send_udp_message with socket as client.socket and data as data
    If bytes_sent is greater than 0:
    Set client.statistics.messages_sent to client.statistics.messages_sent 1
    Return true Return false

Process called "receive_udp_client_message" that takes client as UDPClient returns UDPMessage:
    If client.connection_state is not equal to "connected":
    Return None Let message be receive_udp_message with socket as client.socket
    If message is not None:
    Set client.statistics.messages_received to client.statistics.messages_received 1 Return message

Process called "disconnect_udp_client" that takes client as UDPClient:
    close_udp_socket with socket as client.socket
    Set client.connection_state to "disconnected"

Note: Multicast support
Process called "join_multicast_group" that takes socket as UDPSocket and group_address as String and interface_address as String returns Boolean:
    If not is_multicast_address with ip_address as group_address:
    Return false Note: Add to socket's multicast groups list
    If group_address not in socket.multicast_groups:
    Add group_address to socket.multicast_groups Note: Configure socket for multicast
    set_udp_socket_option with socket as socket and option as "IP_ADD_MEMBERSHIP" and value as group_address
    return true Return false

Process called "leave_multicast_group" that takes socket as UDPSocket and group_address as String returns Boolean:
    If group_address in socket.multicast_groups:
    Remove group_address from socket.multicast_groups
    set_udp_socket_option with socket as socket and option as "IP_DROP_MEMBERSHIP" and value as group_address
    Return true Return false

Process called "send_multicast_message" that takes socket as UDPSocket and data as String and group_address as String and port as Integer returns Integer:
    If not is_multicast_address with ip_address as group_address:
    Return 0 Let multicast_endpoint be UDPEndpoint with ip_address as group_address and port as port and address_family as "IPv4" and interface_name as ""
    Return send_udp_message_to with socket as socket and data as data and destination as multicast_endpoint

Process called "create_multicast_group" that takes group_address as String and port as Integer and ttl as Integer returns UDPMulticastGroup:
    Return UDPMulticastGroup with:
    group_address as group_address
    group_port as port
    interface_address as "0.0.0.0"
    members as list
    ttl as ttl
    is_active as true
    creation_time as DateTime.now()

Note: Broadcast support
Process called "enable_broadcast" that takes socket as UDPSocket returns Boolean:
    Set socket.broadcast_enabled to true
    Return set_udp_socket_option with socket as socket and option as "SO_BROADCAST" and value as true

Process called "send_broadcast_message" that takes socket as UDPSocket and data as String and port as Integer returns Integer:
    If not socket.broadcast_enabled:
    Return 0 Let broadcast_endpoint be UDPEndpoint with ip_address as "255.255.255.255" and port as port and address_family as "IPv4" and interface_name as ""
    Return send_udp_message_to with socket as socket and data as data and destination as broadcast_endpoint

Process called "send_subnet_broadcast" that takes socket as UDPSocket and data as String and subnet as String and port as Integer returns Integer:
    Let broadcast_address be calculate_broadcast_address with subnet as subnet
    Let broadcast_endpoint be UDPEndpoint with ip_address as broadcast_address and port as port and address_family as "IPv4" and interface_name as ""
    Return send_udp_message_to with socket as socket and data as data and destination as broadcast_endpoint

Note: Socket configuration and options
Process called "create_default_udp_options" returns UDPOptions:
    Return UDPOptions with:
    receive_buffer_size as 65536
    send_buffer_size as 65536
    receive_timeout as 30.0
    send_timeout as 30.0
    reuse_address as false
    reuse_port as false
    broadcast as false
    multicast_ttl as 1
    multicast_loop as true
    dont_fragment as false
    type_of_service as 0

Process called "set_udp_socket_option" that takes socket as UDPSocket and option as String and value as Any returns Boolean:
    Match option:
    When "SO_RCVBUF":
    Set socket.options.receive_buffer_size to value as Integer
    When "SO_SNDBUF":
    Set socket.options.send_buffer_size to value as Integer
    When "SO_RCVTIMEO":
    Set socket.options.receive_timeout to value as Float
    When "SO_SNDTIMEO":
    Set socket.options.send_timeout to value as Float
    When "SO_REUSEADDR":
    Set socket.options.reuse_address to value as Boolean
    When "SO_REUSEPORT":
    Set socket.options.reuse_port to value as Boolean
    When "SO_BROADCAST":
    Set socket.options.broadcast to value as Boolean
    Set socket.broadcast_enabled to value as Boolean
    When "IP_MULTICAST_TTL":
    Set socket.options.multicast_ttl to value as Integer
    When "IP_MULTICAST_LOOP":
    Set socket.options.multicast_loop to value as Boolean
    Otherwise:
    Return false Return true

Process called "configure_udp_server_socket" that takes server as UDPServer:
    set_udp_socket_option with socket as server.socket and option as "SO_REUSEADDR" and value as true If server.server_options.enable_broadcast:
    enable_broadcast with socket as server.socket If server.server_options.enable_multicast:
    set_udp_socket_option with socket as server.socket and option as "IP_MULTICAST_LOOP" and value as true

Note: Message queue management
Process called "create_udp_message_queue" returns UDPMessageQueue:
    Return UDPMessageQueue with:
    queue_id as generate_udp_message_queue_id()
    messages as list
    max_size as 1000
    current_size as 0
    total_received as 0
    total_sent as 0
    dropped_messages as 0
    queue_full_count as 0

Process called "add_message_to_queue" that takes queue as UDPMessageQueue and message as UDPMessage and is_outgoing as Boolean:
    If queue.current_size is greater than or equal to queue.max_size:
    Note: Drop oldest message to make room
    Remove queue.messages[0]
    Set queue.dropped_messages to queue.dropped_messages 1
    Set queue.queue_full_count to queue.queue_full_count 1
    Set queue.current_size to queue.current_size - 1 Add message to queue.messages
    Set queue.current_size to queue.current_size 1 If is_outgoing:
    Set queue.total_sent to queue.total_sent 1
    Otherwise:
    Set queue.total_received to queue.total_received 1

Process called "get_message_from_queue" that takes queue as UDPMessageQueue returns UDPMessage:
    If queue.current_size is equal to 0:
    Return None Let message be queue.messages[0]
    Remove queue.messages[0]
    Set queue.current_size to queue.current_size - 1 Return message

Note: Access control and security
Process called "create_default_udp_access_control" returns UDPAccessControl:
    Return UDPAccessControl with:
    enabled as false
    allowed_sources as list
    blocked_sources as list
    allowed_ports as list
    blocked_ports as list
    rate_limits as dictionary
    message_size_limit as 65536
    connection_limits as dictionary

Process called "check_udp_access" that takes access_control as UDPAccessControl and source as UDPEndpoint returns Boolean:
    If not access_control.enabled:
    Return true Note: Check blocked sources
    For each blocked_ip in access_control.blocked_sources:
    If source.ip_address is equal to blocked_ip:
    Return false Note: Check allowed sources if specified
    If Collections.List.length with lst as access_control.allowed_sources is greater than 0:
    Let is_allowed be false
    For each allowed_ip in access_control.allowed_sources:
    If source.ip_address is equal to allowed_ip:
    Set is_allowed to true
    Break
    If not is_allowed:
    Return false Return true

Process called "apply_udp_rate_limit" that takes access_control as UDPAccessControl and source_ip as String returns Boolean:
    If source_ip not in access_control.rate_limits:
    Set access_control.rate_limits[source_ip] to create_default_udp_rate_limit() Let rate_limit be access_control.rate_limits[source_ip] Note: Check if we're in a new time window
    Let current_time be DateTime.now()
    Let window_elapsed be DateTime.difference_in_seconds with start as rate_limit.window_start and end as current_time If window_elapsed is greater than or equal to rate_limit.window_duration:
    Set rate_limit.window_start to current_time
    Set rate_limit.current_message_count to 0
    Set rate_limit.current_byte_count to 0
    Set rate_limit.exceeded to false Set rate_limit.current_message_count to rate_limit.current_message_count 1 If rate_limit.current_message_count is greater than rate_limit.messages_per_second:
    Set rate_limit.exceeded to true
    Return false Return true

Note: Performance monitoring
Process called "create_udp_statistics" returns UDPStatistics:
    Return UDPStatistics with:
    messages_sent as 0
    messages_received as 0
    bytes_sent as 0
    bytes_received as 0
    send_errors as 0
    receive_errors as 0
    dropped_messages as 0
    duplicate_messages as 0
    out_of_order_messages as 0
    checksum_errors as 0
    fragmentation_events as 0
    reassembly_failures as 0

Process called "create_udp_server_statistics" returns UDPServerStatistics:
    Return UDPServerStatistics with:
    total_clients as 0
    active_clients as 0
    messages_processed as 0
    bytes_processed as 0
    processing_errors as 0
    uptime as 0
    peak_clients as 0
    average_message_size as 0.0
    peak_message_rate as 0

Process called "create_udp_client_statistics" returns UDPClientStatistics:
    Return UDPClientStatistics with:
    connection_attempts as 0
    successful_connections as 0
    failed_connections as 0
    messages_sent as 0
    messages_received as 0
    timeouts as 0
    retries as 0

Process called "get_udp_socket_info" that takes socket as UDPSocket returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary with:
    "socket_id" as socket.socket_id
    "local_endpoint" as format_udp_endpoint with endpoint as socket.local_endpoint
    "remote_endpoint" as format_udp_endpoint with endpoint as socket.remote_endpoint
    "state" as udp_socket_state_to_string with state as socket.state
    "messages_sent" as socket.statistics.messages_sent
    "messages_received" as socket.statistics.messages_received
    "bytes_sent" as socket.statistics.bytes_sent
    "bytes_received" as socket.statistics.bytes_received
    "multicast_groups" as Collections.List.length with lst as socket.multicast_groups
    "broadcast_enabled" as socket.broadcast_enabled

Note: Client registry management
Process called "create_udp_client_registry" returns UDPClientRegistry:
    Return UDPClientRegistry with:
    registry_id as generate_udp_client_registry_id()
    clients as dictionary
    max_clients as 10000
    cleanup_interval as 300
    last_cleanup as DateTime.now()

Process called "update_client_registry" that takes registry as UDPClientRegistry and endpoint as UDPEndpoint:
    Let client_key be format_udp_endpoint with endpoint as endpoint If client_key in registry.clients:
    Let client_info be registry.clients[client_key]
    Set client_info.last_seen to DateTime.now()
    Set client_info.message_count to client_info.message_count 1
    Set client_info.is_active to true
    Otherwise:
    If Collections.Dictionary.size with dict as registry.clients is less than registry.max_clients:
    Let client_info be UDPClientInfo with:
    client_endpoint as endpoint
    first_seen as DateTime.now()
    last_seen as DateTime.now()
    message_count as 1
    bytes_transferred as 0
    is_active as true Set registry.clients[client_key] to client_info

Process called "cleanup_client_registry" that takes registry as UDPClientRegistry:
    Let current_time be DateTime.now()
    Let cleanup_threshold be DateTime.subtract_seconds with datetime as current_time and seconds as 3600 Let clients_to_remove be list For each client_key and client_info in registry.clients:
    If client_info.last_seen is less than cleanup_threshold:
    Add client_key to clients_to_remove For each client_key in clients_to_remove:
    Remove client_key from registry.clients Set registry.last_cleanup to current_time

Note: Utility functions
Process called "generate_udp_socket_id" returns String:
    Return "udp_socket_" followed by String.from with value as DateTime.now().timestamp

Process called "generate_udp_server_id" returns String:
    Return "udp_server_" followed by String.from with value as DateTime.now().timestamp

Process called "generate_udp_client_id" returns String:
    Return "udp_client_" followed by String.from with value as DateTime.now().timestamp

Process called "generate_udp_message_queue_id" returns String:
    Return "udp_queue_" followed by String.from with value as DateTime.now().timestamp

Process called "generate_udp_client_registry_id" returns String:
    Return "udp_registry_" followed by String.from with value as DateTime.now().timestamp

Process called "create_udp_message" that takes source as UDPEndpoint and destination as UDPEndpoint and data as String returns UDPMessage:
    Return UDPMessage with:
    message_id as generate_udp_message_id()
    source_endpoint as source
    destination_endpoint as destination
    data as data
    length as String.length with str as data
    timestamp as DateTime.now()
    ttl as 64
    priority as 0
    checksum as calculate_udp_checksum with data as data

Process called "generate_udp_message_id" returns String:
    Return "udp_msg_" followed by String.from with value as DateTime.now().timestamp

Process called "create_default_udp_server_options" returns UDPServerOptions:
    Return UDPServerOptions with:
    max_message_size as 65536
    message_timeout as 30.0
    enable_broadcast as false
    enable_multicast as false
    thread_pool_size as 10
    rate_limiting as false
    max_clients as 1000

Process called "create_default_udp_client_options" returns UDPClientOptions:
    Return UDPClientOptions with:
    connect_timeout as 10.0
    retry_count as 3
    retry_delay as 1.0
    keep_alive_interval as 60.0
    automatic_reconnect as false

Process called "create_default_udp_retry_policy" returns UDPRetryPolicy:
    Return UDPRetryPolicy with:
    max_retries as 3
    initial_delay as 1.0
    max_delay as 30.0
    backoff_multiplier as 2.0
    jitter as true

Process called "create_default_udp_rate_limit" returns UDPRateLimit:
    Return UDPRateLimit with:
    messages_per_second as 100
    bytes_per_second as 1048576
    current_message_count as 0
    current_byte_count as 0
    window_start as DateTime.now()
    window_duration as 1.0
    exceeded as false

Process called "format_udp_endpoint" that takes endpoint as UDPEndpoint returns String:
    If endpoint.ip_address is equal to "":
    Return "*:0"
    Return endpoint.ip_address followed by ":" followed by String.from with value as endpoint.port

Process called "udp_socket_state_to_string" that takes state as UDPSocketState returns String:
    Match state:
    When Created:
    Return "CREATED"
    When Bound:
    Return "BOUND"
    When Connected:
    Return "CONNECTED"
    When Listening:
    Return "LISTENING"
    When Closed:
    Return "CLOSED"

Process called "is_multicast_address" that takes ip_address as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if IP is in multicast range (224.0.0.0 to 239.255.255.255)
    Let parts be String.split with str as ip_address and separator as "."
    If Collections.List.length with lst as parts is equal to 4:
    Let first_octet be Integer.from with value as Float.from with value as parts[0]
    Return first_octet is greater than or equal to 224 and first_octet is less than or equal to 239
    Return false

Process called "calculate_broadcast_address" that takes subnet as String returns String:
    Note: Simplified broadcast calculation
    If String.contains with str as subnet and substring as "/24":
    Let network_part be String.split with str as subnet and separator as "/"[0]
    Let network_parts be String.split with str as network_part and separator as "."
    If Collections.List.length with lst as network_parts is equal to 4:
    Return network_parts[0] followed by "." followed by network_parts[1] followed by "." followed by network_parts[2] followed by ".255"
    Return "255.255.255.255"

Process called "calculate_udp_checksum" that takes data as String returns Integer:
    Note: Simplified UDP checksum calculation
    Let checksum be 0
    For each char in String.to_chars with str as data:
    Set checksum to checksum String.char_code with char as char
    Return checksum modulo 65536

Process called "create_socket_address_from_udp_endpoint" that takes endpoint as UDPEndpoint returns Socket.SocketAddress:
    Return Socket.SocketAddress with:
    family as Socket.IPv4
    ip_address as endpoint.ip_address
    port as endpoint.port
    unix_path as ""
    scope_id as 0

Process called "create_udp_endpoint_from_socket_address" that takes address as Socket.SocketAddress returns UDPEndpoint:
    Return UDPEndpoint with:
    ip_address as address.ip_address
    port as address.port
    address_family as "IPv4"
    interface_name as ""

Process called "determine_message_type" that takes data as String returns String:
    Note: Simple message type detection based on content
    If String.starts_with with str as data and prefix as "REQUEST":
    Return "request"
    If String.starts_with with str as data and prefix as "RESPONSE":
    Return "response"
    If String.starts_with with str as data and prefix as "HEARTBEAT":
    Return "heartbeat"
    Return "unknown"

Process called "process_udp_message_with_handler" that takes server as UDPServer and message as UDPMessage and handler as String:
    Note: Process message with specified handler
    Match handler:
    When "echo_handler":
    send_udp_server_response with server as server and response_data as "ECHO: " followed by message.data and client_endpoint as message.source_endpoint
    When "time_handler":
    send_udp_server_response with server as server and response_data as "TIME: " followed by String.from with value as DateTime.now().timestamp and client_endpoint as message.source_endpoint
    Otherwise:
    send_udp_server_response with server as server and response_data as "ACK" and client_endpoint as message.source_endpoint